clawssh — run Claude Code on remote machines over SSH

Full native TUI, zero installation on the remote. Patches
Claude Code's child_process.spawn via NODE_OPTIONS to route
tool commands through an SSH tunnel.

  $ clawssh root@192.168.1.10
  [clawssh] Connected — remote cwd: /root
  [clawssh] Using Claude Code from ~/.npm-packages/.../cli.js
   ▐▛███▜▌   Claude Code v2.1.84
  ▝▜█████▛▘  Opus 4.6 (1M context) · Claude Max
    ▘▘ ▝▝    /root

  ❯ what machine is this?

  ⏺ Bash(uname -a)
    ⎿  Linux prod-web-01 6.1.0 #1 SMP x86_64 GNU/Linux

  ❯ read /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

  ⏺ Read(/etc/nginx/nginx.conf)
    ⎿  worker_processes auto;
       events { worker_connections 1024; }
       ...

HOW IT WORKS

  1. SSH connection — connects to the target, detects
     remote home dir, sets up ControlMaster for connection
     reuse with per-session random socket paths under
     ~/.clawssh/sockets/ (mode 0700).

  2. Spawn interception — patch.cjs is injected via
     NODE_OPTIONS=--require into Claude Code and all its
     worker threads. Intercepts child_process.spawn with
     Object.defineProperty getters. Claude's Bash tool
     wraps commands as zsh -c "... eval 'COMMAND' ...".
     The patch extracts the eval'd command and runs it
     via ssh target -- bash -c 'cd /remote && COMMAND'.

  3. fs interception — readFile, writeFile, stat, readdir,
     mkdir, realpath, unlink, rm all patched. Paths under
     the remote cwd go through SSH. Everything else stays
     local. Real stat values (size, mtime) from the remote.

  4. Cleanup — shell-snapshot sourcing and cwd-tracking
     stripped from commands before sending to remote.
     SSH absorbs SIGTERM on cancel, so the patch tracks
     kill signals and reports them as signal-based exit
     so Claude shows "Cancelled" properly.

Claude's internal operations (security, which, git, npm,
codesign, ripgrep) all stay local. Only tool-dispatched
commands go remote.

USAGE

  clawssh [SSH-FLAGS...] <USER@HOST> [CLAUDE-FLAGS...]

SSH flags go before the target, Claude flags go after.

  clawssh root@192.168.1.10
  clawssh -i ~/.ssh/key -p 2222 dev@server
  clawssh -J jumpbox root@internal --resume
  clawssh -p 2222 dev@box --model opus -c

INSTALL

  deno install -A --global --name clawssh src/index.ts

Requires Deno and Node.js (for Claude Code's cli.js).
The remote machine needs nothing — just an SSH server.

ENVIRONMENT

  CLAWSSH_CLAUDE_PATH   override path to Claude cli.js
  CLAWSSH_NODE_PATH     override path to node binary
  CLAWSSH_DEBUG=1       log intercepted tool calls
  DENO_NO_PROMPT=1      suppress Deno permission prompts

WHAT RUNS WHERE

  Remote (via SSH):
    Bash tool commands — ls, cat, grep, find, systemctl,
    docker ps, nginx -t, anything Claude decides to run.
    File tool operations — Read, Write, Edit on paths
    under the remote working directory.

  Local (passthrough):
    Claude internals — security (keychain), which, git,
    npm, gh, codesign, ps, ripgrep. Auth, config, session
    files, temp task output.

HARDENING

  - Per-session random socket path in ~/.clawssh/sockets/
    with mode 0700 (no predictable /tmp paths)
  - Null byte stripping and control character rejection
    on all paths before shell quoting
  - 30s timeout on all SSH operations with single retry
    on transient failures (connection reset, broken pipe)
  - Real stat values (size, mtime) from remote, not fakes
  - fs routing by allowlist (only remoteCwd subtree goes
    remote) not denylist
  - ssh -O exit on SIGINT and normal exit to prevent
    stale socket password prompts
